import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='location', y='precipitation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across locations?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, ax=ax, label='Max Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, ax=ax, label='Min Temperature')
    plt.axhline(y=data['temp_max'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Temperature')
    plt.axhline(y=data['temp_min'].min(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='Min Temperature')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day
    data = data.drop(columns=['date'])
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    sns.catplot(x='location', y='counts', hue='weather', data=data, kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition in each location?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
